WEBVTT

00:04.526 --> 00:04.700
.

00:04.743 --> 00:07.137
- In the nation's
largest city,

00:07.181 --> 00:09.879
the vicious and violent
members of the underworld

00:09.922 --> 00:11.489
are hunted by the detectives

00:11.533 --> 00:14.710
of the Organized Crime
Control Bureau.

00:14.753 --> 00:16.494
These are their stories.

00:18.061 --> 00:19.758
- What's your interest
in Damon's case?

00:19.802 --> 00:22.065
- I want you to partner
with my old firm.

00:22.109 --> 00:23.284
- And what's in it for you?

00:23.327 --> 00:25.547
[suspenseful music]

00:25.590 --> 00:26.765
- Who's that?

00:26.809 --> 00:28.724
- Edmund Ross,
hedge fund billionaire.

00:28.767 --> 00:30.465
- Your friend, Flutura,

00:30.508 --> 00:32.293
she's a lot more
than a party planner.

00:32.336 --> 00:34.034
- They're bidding on the girls.

00:34.077 --> 00:35.818
- Human trafficking.
We're moving in.

00:35.861 --> 00:36.862
- [sobs]

00:36.906 --> 00:41.345
♪

00:41.389 --> 00:44.740
- I'm a police officer.
You're safe now.

00:44.783 --> 00:46.263
- Drop the weapon, Ross.

00:46.307 --> 00:48.831
We are way more interested
in Kosta than we are in you.

00:48.874 --> 00:50.398
- Ross keeps a black book

00:50.441 --> 00:52.095
of everyone
who attends his parties.

00:53.836 --> 00:55.098
- How did this happen?

00:55.142 --> 00:58.101
- There's a rat
in this organization.

01:00.234 --> 01:02.497
- Whoa.
[laughs]

01:02.540 --> 01:05.195
- Lightweight?
- [laughs]

01:05.239 --> 01:07.980
Okay, you'll see. You'll see.

01:08.024 --> 01:08.981
- Never had
that problem before.

01:09.025 --> 01:11.636
- Oh, really?
- Oh, come on.

01:11.680 --> 01:13.899
- Oh, you saved me again,
Eddie.

01:13.943 --> 01:17.642
- Well, when you call--
- Drunk, I'm drunk.

01:17.686 --> 01:19.209
- Well, drunk or not,
when you call,

01:19.253 --> 01:21.211
I'm at your disposal.

01:21.255 --> 01:23.213
- We drink Raki,

01:23.257 --> 01:27.522
nectar of the Albanian gods.

01:27.565 --> 01:28.740
- Yeah.

01:30.002 --> 01:32.396
- Well, yeah, 90 proof.
That's some nectar.

01:40.796 --> 01:45.148
- The jukebox is why I had Albi
take over this place.

01:45.192 --> 01:47.803
- Ain't no rock and roll
in Albania?

01:50.458 --> 01:54.636
- Mm. Not like this.

01:54.679 --> 01:55.941
New wave.

01:55.985 --> 01:58.944
[Blondie's "Call Me"]

01:58.988 --> 02:05.864
♪

02:08.345 --> 02:11.914
- ♪ Color me
your color, baby ♪

02:11.957 --> 02:15.047
♪ Color me your car

02:15.091 --> 02:18.529
♪ Color me
your color, darling ♪

02:18.573 --> 02:21.663
♪ I know who you are

02:21.706 --> 02:24.448
♪ Come up
off your color chart ♪

02:24.492 --> 02:28.800
- When I was 15,
this was my favorite song.

02:28.844 --> 02:32.108
- You know what it's about?
- Of course.

02:32.152 --> 02:34.328
It's about a woman
who wants a man.

02:34.371 --> 02:37.592
- Well, it's about a call girl.

02:37.635 --> 02:39.507
- You're making an assumption.

02:39.550 --> 02:41.857
You don't know anything
about her.

02:41.900 --> 02:43.424
- No, it's a prostitute.

02:43.467 --> 02:45.208
You know, the girls
at the party the other night.

02:45.252 --> 02:49.691
♪

02:49.734 --> 02:53.825
- They're not prostitutes.
- Okay.

02:56.350 --> 02:58.221
I didn't mean
to hurt your feelings.

02:58.265 --> 02:59.875
- You did.

03:02.051 --> 03:03.270
- ♪ Emotions come

03:03.313 --> 03:05.620
♪ I don't know why

03:05.663 --> 03:10.320
♪ Cover up love's alibi

03:10.364 --> 03:12.801
- Why you care?
- I don't care.

03:12.844 --> 03:14.324
I'm just trying
to make dumb conversation.

03:14.368 --> 03:16.718
I apologize.

03:21.288 --> 03:23.681
- Let's converse like this.

03:27.729 --> 03:31.341
You know, it would be
a lot worse for the girls

03:31.385 --> 03:33.996
if they
didn't have me involved.

03:34.039 --> 03:37.391
- What do you mean a lot worse?
How so?

03:37.434 --> 03:41.351
- I protect them
from Albanian men

03:41.395 --> 03:45.268
because they're derra--pigs.

03:45.312 --> 03:47.705
- Well, look, I don't know
nothing about Albanian men,

03:47.749 --> 03:51.187
but those guys
at the party the other night...

03:51.231 --> 03:56.975
♪

03:57.019 --> 04:01.545
- The year this song came out
was the year I was sold.

04:01.589 --> 04:04.113
[solemn music]

04:04.156 --> 04:05.723
The men my father sold me to--

04:05.767 --> 04:07.595
- Wait a minute. Wait a minute.

04:07.638 --> 04:10.206
Wait--wait a minute.
Your father?

04:10.250 --> 04:12.948
What do you mean your father?
- On the boat to America...

04:12.991 --> 04:16.517
♪

04:16.560 --> 04:19.433
The men had their way with me,

04:19.476 --> 04:21.783
sometimes three or four
in one night.

04:24.655 --> 04:26.744
Only one man didn't hurt me.

04:28.616 --> 04:30.966
He was supposed to take me
to the warehouse

04:31.009 --> 04:34.404
where they kept the girls,

04:34.448 --> 04:37.538
but instead,

04:37.581 --> 04:42.499
he took me home and married me.

04:44.849 --> 04:46.503
- Albi.

04:48.418 --> 04:50.333
Albi saved you.

04:52.161 --> 04:53.902
- Maybe I saved him.

04:58.515 --> 05:00.822
All men are pigs.

05:02.911 --> 05:06.349
Once in a while,
one of you comes through.

05:11.180 --> 05:13.487
[metal clattering]

05:13.530 --> 05:15.227
Is someone out there?

05:15.271 --> 05:18.187
[suspenseful music]

05:18.230 --> 05:22.452
♪

05:22.496 --> 05:24.585
If it's Albi, he'll kill you!

05:26.195 --> 05:27.805
- Hey. Hey!

05:33.420 --> 05:34.595
What are you doing?

05:34.638 --> 05:37.337
Who are you? Who sent you?

05:37.380 --> 05:42.385
Hey, answer me. Who are you?

05:42.429 --> 05:45.388
What do you want?
- Eddie Wagner.

05:45.432 --> 05:47.477
- Last time. Who are you?

05:47.521 --> 05:49.174
- I'm your son.

05:49.218 --> 05:51.960
[dramatic music]

05:52.003 --> 05:55.006
- Hey, look, I don't know
what you want or who you are,

05:55.050 --> 05:56.965
but you better disappear,

05:57.008 --> 05:58.575
or I'm gonna
make you disappear.

05:58.619 --> 06:01.535
Get out of here.
Get out of here!

06:05.626 --> 06:07.454
- Who was it?

06:07.497 --> 06:09.891
- Just some kid
looking to jack the bar.

06:09.934 --> 06:10.935
Come on.

06:13.242 --> 06:14.678
Keep drinking.

06:18.160 --> 06:21.206
[tense music]

06:21.250 --> 06:28.170
♪

07:09.516 --> 07:10.691
- Mama.

07:10.734 --> 07:12.519
- Oh, good,
just in time for breakfast.

07:12.562 --> 07:15.043
- Yeah, no, I can't.
I'm just here to check on Eli.

07:15.086 --> 07:16.827
- Yeah, he's still
not talking to me.

07:16.871 --> 07:18.699
- All right.
I'll try and fix that.

07:18.742 --> 07:21.266
- I'll fix you some eggs.
- I don't have time.

07:21.310 --> 07:23.486
- You've got time
to eat a couple of eggs.

07:25.401 --> 07:27.447
- All right, sleepyhead,
rise and shine.

07:27.490 --> 07:28.926
Let's go.

07:28.970 --> 07:30.798
- Dad, God,
give me a break.

07:30.841 --> 07:33.975
- Want me to give you a break?
Why you still asleep?

07:34.018 --> 07:36.020
- I was up late prepping
for a chem test, okay?

07:36.064 --> 07:37.282
- Okay.

07:37.326 --> 07:38.675
- Check the cameras
if you don't believe me.

07:38.719 --> 07:40.198
- Well, those cameras
are there for your safety,

07:40.242 --> 07:42.723
and Jet only flags something
for me if it's suspicious.

07:42.766 --> 07:44.464
- God, it's like East Germany

07:44.507 --> 07:46.988
in the Cold War,
and you're the Stasi.

07:47.031 --> 07:48.555
- Look, it may seem
like I'm policing you,

07:48.598 --> 07:52.515
and, well, okay, I am,
but look, once I'm back home,

07:52.559 --> 07:56.519
you and me, we can come up
with a better system.

07:56.563 --> 07:59.087
- Once you're back home?
- Yeah.

07:59.130 --> 08:02.264
- Where's Grandma gonna sleep?

08:02.307 --> 08:04.135
- Your eggs are ready.

08:09.184 --> 08:11.534
- Transnational organized crime
poses one of

08:11.578 --> 08:13.536
the greatest threats
to New Yorkers' safety,

08:13.580 --> 08:16.365
our health,
our democratic institutions,

08:16.408 --> 08:18.454
and our economic well-being.

08:18.498 --> 08:21.283
Now we're seeing an even
more pernicious alliance

08:21.326 --> 08:24.025
forming between
these criminal organizations

08:24.068 --> 08:26.462
and our so-called pillars
of Wall Street.

08:26.506 --> 08:27.942
Last week,
a hedge fund billionaire

08:27.985 --> 08:29.334
by the name of Edmund Ross

08:29.378 --> 08:31.554
was implicated
in a sex trafficking ring

08:31.598 --> 08:34.078
run by a ruthless
Albanian mafia outfit

08:34.122 --> 08:35.993
known as
the Kosta Organization.

08:36.037 --> 08:37.604
As Governor of New York...

08:37.647 --> 08:39.519
- Really wish
he hadn't done that.

08:39.562 --> 08:41.085
- [chuckles]
What do you expect?

08:41.129 --> 08:42.391
Bleeding heart liberal.

08:42.434 --> 08:43.697
Sees a billionaire
in the headlines,

08:43.740 --> 08:45.350
of course he's gonna
jump all over him.

08:45.394 --> 08:47.483
- The Ross arrest was
heavily reported on the news.

08:47.527 --> 08:49.485
- Yeah, but nobody
ever mentioned the Albanians.

08:49.529 --> 08:50.965
- Yeah, that's 'cause we were
keeping them on the DL.

08:51.008 --> 08:52.619
He must have a mole downtown.

08:52.662 --> 08:55.012
- How the hell did we not know
Eddie Wagner has a son.

08:55.056 --> 08:56.492
- Excuse me?
- A son?

08:56.536 --> 08:59.321
- Yeah, a son.
I'm with Flutura last night.

08:59.364 --> 09:00.496
I'm trying to get her
to tell me

09:00.540 --> 09:02.846
about the K-O
trafficking operations,

09:02.890 --> 09:05.240
which I think I recorded

09:05.283 --> 09:07.242
with your super
secret agent watch there,

09:07.285 --> 09:10.724
and I'm interrupted by some
juvie looking stalker kid

09:10.767 --> 09:12.421
who claims that he's
Eddie Wagner's son.

09:12.464 --> 09:15.555
So, I ask again, is it true?
How'd that happen?

09:15.598 --> 09:19.036
Because this arose
with a Maine driver's license.

09:19.080 --> 09:21.256
Louis Chinaski.
- Run it.

09:21.299 --> 09:23.606
[suspenseful music]

09:23.650 --> 09:25.390
- Louis Edward Chinaski,

09:25.434 --> 09:28.393
19 years old
from Bangor, Maine.

09:28.437 --> 09:31.658
Louis' mother, Janice Chinaski,
OD'd in 2011.

09:31.701 --> 09:34.051
Louis went into
the foster system at age six.

09:34.095 --> 09:38.316
And it looks like
there was a male,

09:38.360 --> 09:42.364
one E Wagner, who was
in and out of the household.

09:42.407 --> 09:44.061
- Hence Louis' middle name.

09:44.105 --> 09:47.238
- Which makes it very likely
that Eddie was his father.

09:47.282 --> 09:50.415
- Apologies for missing it
on my original search.

09:50.459 --> 09:52.504
No excuses, but most of what

09:52.548 --> 09:54.811
I was able to find
on Wagner was analog.

09:54.855 --> 09:57.031
- Anything else?

09:57.074 --> 09:58.598
- A domestic incident report

09:58.641 --> 10:00.687
that shows the kid
landed in the ER,

10:00.730 --> 10:03.298
which is how
Child Services got involved.

10:03.341 --> 10:07.171
- Fractured ribs,
nose, orbital bone.

10:09.304 --> 10:11.611
Six years old.

10:11.654 --> 10:13.830
Looks like not only
am I an arsonist,

10:13.874 --> 10:15.092
I'm also a child abuser.

10:15.136 --> 10:16.746
- Stabler, don't get invested
in this kid.

10:16.790 --> 10:19.923
- I'm not invested.
I scared him away.

10:19.967 --> 10:21.577
He came looking
for his piece of trash father,

10:21.621 --> 10:23.666
and I convinced him
I'm still a piece of trash.

10:23.710 --> 10:26.626
- Good, because if it risks
blowing your cover,

10:26.669 --> 10:28.236
we're gonna have to pick him up
and take him off the street.

10:28.279 --> 10:31.065
- Hey, Jet,
no more surprises, yeah?

10:31.108 --> 10:32.762
- Copy.
- Okay.

10:32.806 --> 10:34.329
Where are we with Ross?

10:34.372 --> 10:35.983
- Brewster and I were waiting
on you to interrogate him.

10:36.026 --> 10:37.375
We gotta flip this guy.

10:37.419 --> 10:38.812
- DA's Office concurs
that we have enough

10:38.855 --> 10:40.596
to indict Briscu and Bogdani.

10:40.640 --> 10:42.250
- We're not moving
on Albi or Reggie

10:42.293 --> 10:44.905
until we have enough
to indict Kosta.

10:44.948 --> 10:47.734
All the dominoes fall in a row.
That's what Sergeant Bell said.

10:47.777 --> 10:50.432
- Kosta is the endgame.

10:50.475 --> 10:53.130
- We've already told you.
We're not interested.

10:53.174 --> 10:57.395
- What was your arrangement
with the Kosta Organization?

10:57.439 --> 10:59.354
How long were they
supplying girls to you?

11:00.834 --> 11:02.618
- The who?

11:02.662 --> 11:05.665
- Ask him how he chose
his party planner.

11:05.708 --> 11:07.884
- Flutura Briscu
put together an event

11:07.928 --> 11:10.147
for the Mersham Foundation.

11:10.191 --> 11:12.410
I was one of the honorees.

11:12.454 --> 11:13.716
It was an impressive event,

11:13.760 --> 11:15.631
so I hired her
to do my next event.

11:15.675 --> 11:17.720
- I suppose you weren't aware
that Mrs. Briscu is married

11:17.764 --> 11:20.549
to the number two man
in the Kosta Organization.

11:20.592 --> 11:24.771
- As I said, I've never heard
of the Kosta Organization.

11:24.814 --> 11:27.687
- Oh, maybe this
will jog your memory.

11:27.730 --> 11:30.646
♪

11:30.690 --> 11:32.735
- That man
whispering in your ear,

11:32.779 --> 11:34.998
that's Jon Kosta.

11:35.042 --> 11:36.391
You still never heard of him?

11:38.001 --> 11:39.873
- Did he pay the K-O
a flat fee for the girls?

11:39.916 --> 11:42.136
- Or did Kosta also take
a cut of the final sales

11:42.179 --> 11:43.703
after the girls were purchased?

11:43.746 --> 11:46.967
- I had no idea
those girls were being sold.

11:47.010 --> 11:48.664
- That's BS.

11:48.708 --> 11:51.188
Rita was sent to Ross' house
a few days before the party.

11:51.232 --> 11:52.973
You tell him
we've got Rita in custody,

11:53.016 --> 11:55.627
and she is prepared
to testify against him

11:55.671 --> 11:58.021
every assault
that she endured at his hands.

11:58.065 --> 12:03.374
- Some Albanian girl says this.
I say that.

12:05.202 --> 12:06.551
I don't know, Sergeant.

12:06.595 --> 12:08.945
Seems like a case
of he said, she said to me.

12:14.821 --> 12:16.692
- That black book
look familiar?

12:16.736 --> 12:21.871
♪

12:21.915 --> 12:25.092
There are plenty of names
still in this book

12:25.135 --> 12:28.835
that didn't burn up
when you threw it in the fire.

12:28.878 --> 12:32.969
So Mr. Ross,
you have two choices.

12:33.013 --> 12:35.798
One, you can talk to us.

12:35.842 --> 12:39.541
Two, Jon Kosta
and the other important people

12:39.584 --> 12:45.025
in his book are gonna make sure
you don't talk to anyone.

12:45.068 --> 12:51.509
♪

12:51.553 --> 12:53.816
- Right hand up.
Protect, protect.

12:53.860 --> 12:56.036
Keep your guard up.
Joe, come on.

12:56.079 --> 12:57.428
- Hey, Eddie.

12:59.213 --> 13:01.781
- Mjaft, Mjaft.
Stop, stop, stop!

13:01.824 --> 13:03.608
You want to kill
my best fighter?

13:07.874 --> 13:09.876
Didn't tell me
you had a kid, Eddie.

13:09.919 --> 13:12.356
- Probably got a lot of kids
I don't know about.

13:12.400 --> 13:15.838
- Familia.
Know what that means, Eddie?

13:15.882 --> 13:18.188
- Yeah, family.

13:18.232 --> 13:20.234
- Very important
in the Albanian culture,

13:20.277 --> 13:22.410
even if the kid is a bastard.

13:22.453 --> 13:25.152
- He said
I got your boxing genes.

13:25.195 --> 13:26.501
And you know, someday

13:26.544 --> 13:28.590
I could even be
a better fighter than you.

13:28.633 --> 13:29.852
- Well, you're not yet,

13:29.896 --> 13:31.462
and unless you want me
to prove it to you,

13:31.506 --> 13:33.595
you're gonna get the hell
out of here right now.

13:33.638 --> 13:35.858
- Wait, wait, wait!

13:40.341 --> 13:41.951
I, uh...

13:44.127 --> 13:45.259
Uh...

13:45.302 --> 13:48.218
[sentimental music]

13:48.262 --> 13:55.051
♪

13:55.095 --> 13:56.879
- Come here.

13:56.923 --> 13:59.490
What do you want?
You want money?

13:59.534 --> 14:02.450
- No, I don't want money.

14:02.493 --> 14:04.887
Look, a couple of weeks ago,
a friend of mine in Brooklyn,

14:04.931 --> 14:09.457
he sends me a link
about a drug bust in Red Hook.

14:09.500 --> 14:10.545
He said I could stay with him

14:10.588 --> 14:12.982
if I wanted to come
try to find you.

14:13.026 --> 14:15.115
- Great. You found me.

14:15.158 --> 14:17.291
- Yeah, and I'm not
looking for a handout.

14:17.334 --> 14:19.075
You know, I could use a job.

14:19.119 --> 14:20.468
I could, you know,
help out with stuff.

14:20.511 --> 14:21.643
- Don't have no job.
- I'm pretty good with--

14:21.686 --> 14:23.210
- I don't have
a job to give you.

14:23.253 --> 14:25.734
- Hey, kid, this is my gym.

14:25.777 --> 14:28.171
You want to earn a few bucks,
I can find you something to do.

14:28.215 --> 14:31.740
I'm sure Eddie wouldn't mind.
Would you, Eddie?

14:31.783 --> 14:33.394
- No.

14:33.437 --> 14:38.921
♪

14:38.965 --> 14:42.707
Well, Louis Chinaski,
congratulations.

14:45.493 --> 14:47.582
You're the Besa Boxing Gym
spit bucket boy.

14:47.625 --> 14:53.762
♪

14:53.805 --> 14:56.417
- That Ross arrest is really
hitting the nerve of our base.

14:56.460 --> 14:59.899
Who would have thought I'd be
the tough-on-crime candidate?

15:03.293 --> 15:04.947
What can I do for you,
Detective?

15:04.991 --> 15:07.036
- Sergeant. Ayanna Bell.

15:07.080 --> 15:08.777
I was surprised
to hear you calling out

15:08.820 --> 15:11.214
transnational
criminal organizations by name

15:11.258 --> 15:12.868
at your rally this morning.

15:12.912 --> 15:14.609
- I'm a progressive, Sergeant.

15:14.652 --> 15:17.568
That doesn't mean
I'm in favor of crime.

15:19.701 --> 15:22.008
- Unfortunately, we're in
the middle of an investigation.

15:22.051 --> 15:23.879
- The Edmund Ross thing.

15:23.923 --> 15:26.447
- He's a bad guy,
but he wasn't our target.

15:26.490 --> 15:28.753
Our operation
is focused on the TCO

15:28.797 --> 15:32.322
that supplies the girls to him.
- The Albanians.

15:32.366 --> 15:33.541
- It hasn't been
reported anywhere

15:33.584 --> 15:35.586
that it was
an Albanian syndicate,

15:35.630 --> 15:37.023
and we make a point

15:37.066 --> 15:40.896
of not identifying any group
or crew or individuals.

15:40.940 --> 15:42.550
- 'Cause you didn't
want to tip them off.

15:42.593 --> 15:44.030
I get it,
and I certainly didn't mean

15:44.073 --> 15:45.422
to jeopardize
your investigation.

15:45.466 --> 15:46.902
- It's not just that.

15:46.946 --> 15:49.383
When you name check a man
like Jon Kosta

15:49.426 --> 15:51.167
in public the way you did,

15:51.211 --> 15:55.302
you're putting yourself in
a really dangerous situation.

15:55.345 --> 15:57.173
- If I had a nickel for
everyone who doesn't like me

15:57.217 --> 15:59.523
because of a position
I've taken, Sergeant Bell,

15:59.567 --> 16:02.091
I wouldn't have to spend
so much time fundraising.

16:02.135 --> 16:04.354
I do have a bodyguard.

16:04.398 --> 16:05.486
- Only one?

16:05.529 --> 16:06.966
- I didn't even
want to hire him.

16:07.009 --> 16:08.445
My wife insisted.

16:10.708 --> 16:12.101
- Just be careful.

16:19.065 --> 16:24.461
- Someone talked to the NYPD.
I'll figure out who it was.

16:26.202 --> 16:29.336
It could have been
one of Ross' guests,

16:29.379 --> 16:31.642
someone with
a business vendetta,

16:31.686 --> 16:37.257
or someone facing charges
looking to make a deal.

16:37.300 --> 16:39.824
- It's a possibility.

16:39.868 --> 16:42.653
- Well, I gotta consider
another possibility.

16:42.697 --> 16:45.482
[tense music]

16:45.526 --> 16:47.397
someone in this room
is disloyal.

16:47.441 --> 16:53.621
♪

16:53.664 --> 16:54.839
Flutura...

16:56.972 --> 16:58.756
You're the one
who said there's a rat.

17:03.718 --> 17:05.981
Well, there can be
female rats too.

17:08.027 --> 17:11.291
Women are weak.
They gossip, talk too much.

17:11.334 --> 17:13.162
- I'm not weak!

17:13.206 --> 17:16.513
- If you suspect Flutura,
you suspect me, too, Jon.

17:18.167 --> 17:19.516
- Maybe I should.

17:23.477 --> 17:25.566
James.

17:25.609 --> 17:27.263
Stand up.

17:32.138 --> 17:33.791
- Why?

17:37.882 --> 17:40.624
- My grandfather,
he used to say

17:40.668 --> 17:42.713
that you can tell
by the shape of a man's tongue

17:42.757 --> 17:45.020
if he's a liar.

17:48.154 --> 17:50.069
Open your mouth.

17:51.635 --> 17:53.289
Stick your tongue out.

17:57.380 --> 17:58.903
Uh-huh.

18:01.602 --> 18:04.039
[muffled scream]

18:04.083 --> 18:07.260
♪

18:07.303 --> 18:09.349
Well, maybe
my grandfather could tell,

18:09.392 --> 18:11.699
but I have no idea

18:11.742 --> 18:13.831
if my friend James
is innocent or guilty.

18:16.182 --> 18:18.923
This isn't justice.
This is a warning.

18:20.882 --> 18:22.927
And it's child's play
compared to what I'll do

18:22.971 --> 18:25.365
to whoever led the police
to that party.

18:25.408 --> 18:32.589
♪

18:40.162 --> 18:40.336
.

18:40.380 --> 18:42.251
- You really must take
that tongue down, Jon.

18:42.295 --> 18:43.687
It's starting to smell.

18:43.731 --> 18:45.559
- Well, tell me who the rat is,
I'll take it down.

18:47.952 --> 18:52.174
- You know it's not me, right?
- No, you're too smart.

18:52.218 --> 18:54.176
Reggie's too stupid.

18:54.220 --> 18:59.050
You think it was Ashes?
He's an outsider.

18:59.094 --> 19:01.140
- Too small time.

19:01.183 --> 19:02.880
- That's what I think too.

19:02.924 --> 19:04.273
More likely it's one of our own

19:04.317 --> 19:06.536
two-timing us
with another Albanian clan.

19:06.580 --> 19:08.843
- Well, if it is,
I will root them out.

19:10.410 --> 19:12.760
- You know this man Garcia?

19:14.414 --> 19:18.026
- What about him?
- I want him dead.

19:18.069 --> 19:19.288
- What did he do?

19:19.332 --> 19:23.684
- What'd he do?
He insulted our people.

19:23.727 --> 19:26.861
He insulted me
on national television

19:26.904 --> 19:29.820
in front of the whole world.

19:29.864 --> 19:33.737
My name, Albi! My name!

19:33.781 --> 19:36.218
[tense music]

19:36.262 --> 19:39.221
A man doesn't do that
and live to do it again.

19:39.265 --> 19:41.658
- This is not Albania.

19:41.702 --> 19:44.748
You cannot kill
political candidates.

19:46.010 --> 19:49.362
- If you ever read
a history book in your life,

19:49.405 --> 19:51.233
you'd know that they've killed
much more important men

19:51.277 --> 19:53.104
than Teddy Garcia
in this country.

19:53.148 --> 19:55.803
Wagner! Get in here.

20:00.634 --> 20:02.201
I want you to give
your friend Albi here

20:02.244 --> 20:04.420
a lesson on American history.
- Okay.

20:04.464 --> 20:06.596
- How many prominent men
have been assassinated

20:06.640 --> 20:08.207
in this country
in the last century?

20:08.250 --> 20:14.822
♪

20:14.865 --> 20:17.216
- JFK, RFK, MLK,

20:17.259 --> 20:20.088
and they might have got Reagan
if he'd had a K in his name.

20:20.131 --> 20:22.264
- You see, Albi?

20:22.308 --> 20:23.700
If history
has taught us anything,

20:23.744 --> 20:27.574
it's that you can kill
whoever you want in America,

20:27.617 --> 20:29.315
including this
meddling politician Garcia

20:29.358 --> 20:30.707
who calls us the Albanian mafia

20:30.751 --> 20:32.579
and drags my name
through the gutter.

20:34.276 --> 20:36.452
- Who's Garcia?

20:36.496 --> 20:40.456
- [sighs]
Okay, you're kidding me, right?

20:40.500 --> 20:41.979
Don't none of you
watch the news?

20:42.023 --> 20:43.416
- I don't own a TV.

20:43.459 --> 20:46.941
- [sighs]
This is gjakmarrja.

20:48.769 --> 20:50.292
You know what
that means, Wagner?

20:50.336 --> 20:51.859
- Blood feud.

20:51.902 --> 20:57.299
♪

20:57.343 --> 20:58.735
- I got a job for you.

20:58.779 --> 20:59.780
- Okay.

20:59.823 --> 21:01.129
- I want you to find out
who tipped

21:01.172 --> 21:03.305
the police about Edmund Ross.

21:04.959 --> 21:06.613
- I'm on it.

21:06.656 --> 21:08.354
- Convince me it wasn't you.

21:08.397 --> 21:15.535
♪

21:21.671 --> 21:26.546
- I need your advice.
Eddie Wagner.

21:26.589 --> 21:30.593
I know you don't like him,
and I don't understand why,

21:30.637 --> 21:34.684
but I want to know exactly what
you saw in his coffee grounds.

21:34.728 --> 21:37.818
[Albanian pop music playing]

21:37.861 --> 21:40.864
♪

21:40.908 --> 21:44.041
"Grief and tragedy."
Don't they always go together?

21:44.085 --> 21:44.999
- [chuckles]

21:48.872 --> 21:49.960
Zemerimi.

21:50.004 --> 21:51.571
I know. He's angry.

21:55.183 --> 22:00.231
But tell me about love.
Dashuri.

22:00.275 --> 22:03.800
Has Eddie been seeing
one of my girls?

22:03.844 --> 22:05.541
Is he the one
that called the police

22:05.585 --> 22:07.587
and had them taken away?

22:13.419 --> 22:16.596
[suspenseful music]

22:16.639 --> 22:19.076
What? What do you see?

22:19.120 --> 22:26.040
♪

22:34.614 --> 22:36.659
Yes, he saved someone.

22:36.703 --> 22:39.358
He saved me
from being arrested.

22:43.927 --> 22:46.452
Did he save anyone else?

22:46.495 --> 22:53.633
♪

23:06.080 --> 23:07.777
- You're good at that.

23:07.821 --> 23:10.127
- Well, if there's one thing
the Marines teach you

23:10.171 --> 23:12.042
how to do, it's fold.

23:16.395 --> 23:19.093
That guy running
for governor...

23:21.530 --> 23:23.358
Teddy Garcia,

23:23.402 --> 23:25.534
Kosta wants him dead.
- Already on it.

23:25.578 --> 23:27.928
Personally advised him
not to mention

23:27.971 --> 23:29.669
Kosta's name
in any of his speeches.

23:29.712 --> 23:31.410
- Well, it might be too late.

23:31.453 --> 23:33.803
Kosta used the word
"gjakmarrja."

23:36.545 --> 23:38.939
- What's that, like besa?
- It's like blood feud.

23:38.982 --> 23:40.593
When an Albanian
says "gjakmarrja,"

23:40.636 --> 23:42.116
they're not messing around.
They mean it.

23:42.159 --> 23:43.465
They're gonna follow through.

23:43.509 --> 23:45.467
- You think Jon Kosta
would put out a hit?

23:45.511 --> 23:46.773
- Well, seeing as how he has

23:46.816 --> 23:48.818
a man's tongue
nailed to his office wall,

23:48.862 --> 23:50.820
and I saw him cut it
out of the guy's mouth,

23:50.864 --> 23:52.996
I'd say the chances
are pretty good.

23:53.040 --> 23:58.349
♪

23:58.393 --> 24:00.351
- How's your misguided son?

24:00.395 --> 24:02.005
- Eli or Louis?

24:02.049 --> 24:03.529
- The one I told you
to kick to the curb.

24:03.572 --> 24:06.140
I hope you did it.

24:06.183 --> 24:07.924
- Still working on it.

24:07.968 --> 24:10.144
- I'ma send the three-six
to pick him up for jaywalking.

24:10.187 --> 24:12.538
- No, just give me
a little more time with that.

24:12.581 --> 24:15.845
I think Louis is slowly
coming to the realization

24:15.889 --> 24:18.935
that his father is a dirtbag.

24:18.979 --> 24:24.027
♪

24:38.389 --> 24:39.826
- Sergeant Bell.

24:39.869 --> 24:43.220
You brought backup.
Am I in trouble?

24:43.264 --> 24:46.136
- This is my colleague,
Sergeant Brewster.

24:46.180 --> 24:48.530
- Always happy to meet
another voter.

24:48.574 --> 24:49.662
- I'll be voting
for the other guy.

24:49.705 --> 24:51.925
That's not why we're here.

24:51.968 --> 24:53.622
- Jon Kosta
ordered a hit on you.

24:53.666 --> 24:54.841
- We want to put a car

24:54.884 --> 24:56.625
on your office
and one on your house.

24:56.669 --> 24:58.409
- I appreciate
your concern, Sergeant,

24:58.453 --> 25:01.064
whether you vote for me or not,
but that's not what I'm about.

25:01.108 --> 25:04.285
Riding in an armored car
from my heavily-guarded office

25:04.328 --> 25:05.808
to my heavily-guarded home?

25:05.852 --> 25:08.071
- So it's about optics.
- It's about message.

25:08.115 --> 25:10.813
I won't be intimidated
into hiding behind a badge

25:10.857 --> 25:13.555
every time someone I call out
in a speech threatens me

25:13.599 --> 25:16.123
because I call out
a lot of people,

25:16.166 --> 25:17.646
and I'm gonna continue
to call them out

25:17.690 --> 25:20.127
till I'm New York's governor
and long after that.

25:24.784 --> 25:26.742
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I'm in the middle

25:26.786 --> 25:29.832
of date night,
and my wife is winning.

25:29.876 --> 25:30.703
As usual.

25:30.746 --> 25:34.576
[tense music]

25:34.620 --> 25:36.143
- [grunts]

25:36.186 --> 25:41.844
♪

25:46.022 --> 25:46.240
.

25:46.283 --> 25:48.982
[upbeat music playing]

25:49.025 --> 25:50.418
♪

25:50.461 --> 25:52.594
- Hey, whatever this is,
it's gonna stop,

25:52.638 --> 25:53.726
or I'm gonna make it stop.

25:53.769 --> 25:55.031
- Look, I just wanted
to tell you--

25:55.075 --> 25:56.555
- And I just want to tell you

25:56.598 --> 25:59.035
just 'cause I boned your mom
don't make me your father.

25:59.079 --> 26:01.124
Do you understand
what I'm saying to you?

26:01.168 --> 26:02.909
- Look, she was
asking questions about you.

26:02.952 --> 26:04.824
That lady, the one in the bar

26:04.867 --> 26:07.957
that you were
sucking face with.

26:08.001 --> 26:10.525
- Yeah, what kind of questions?
What was she asking about?

26:10.569 --> 26:11.570
- Who's my mother?

26:11.613 --> 26:12.571
When was the last time
I saw you?

26:12.614 --> 26:13.746
Stuff like that.
- What'd you say?

26:13.789 --> 26:15.530
Did you tell her
you were the one in the alley?

26:15.574 --> 26:17.793
- No, I thought
if you didn't tell her,

26:17.837 --> 26:20.753
there must have been a reason
for her not to know.

26:20.796 --> 26:23.625
- You're smart.
All right, I gotta get going.

26:23.669 --> 26:26.541
- You on a job?
- And that's dumb--questions.

26:26.585 --> 26:29.370
Asking too many questions
is trouble.

26:29.413 --> 26:30.458
- Well, I want
to work with you.

26:30.501 --> 26:32.286
I want to learn how you roll.

26:34.331 --> 26:37.639
- How I roll? Okay.

26:37.683 --> 26:39.075
I got a job later today.

26:39.119 --> 26:42.035
Maybe you can help me out.
Go to the hardware store.

26:42.078 --> 26:44.603
Get me a giant can
of lighter fluid.

26:44.646 --> 26:48.345
Bring it back to my place
in an hour.

26:53.002 --> 26:54.961
You know where I live,
don't you?

26:55.004 --> 26:56.179
- Yeah.

27:03.665 --> 27:07.408
- Hey.
Did he say what it's about?

27:07.451 --> 27:09.323
- Just something to do
with Damon's settlement.

27:09.366 --> 27:11.064
I've been working
with this law firm.

27:11.107 --> 27:13.153
- Nova, one minute. I forgot.

27:13.196 --> 27:15.024
[suspenseful music]

27:15.068 --> 27:16.460
Give this to your boss.

27:16.504 --> 27:17.897
Tell him there's more
where that came from.

27:17.940 --> 27:18.985
- Yes, sir.

27:19.028 --> 27:25.556
♪

27:27.863 --> 27:29.169
- Yo, Charlene.

27:29.212 --> 27:31.388
- Bye, Nova. See you soon.

27:35.871 --> 27:38.526
- Ladies, please.

27:43.052 --> 27:45.228
I have news.

27:45.272 --> 27:46.839
- Good news or bad news?

27:46.882 --> 27:49.406
- Well, I'll leave that
for you to decide.

27:51.191 --> 27:55.369
The NYPD is prepared
to offer $750,000

27:55.412 --> 27:57.719
in a settlement
for the unwarranted assault

27:57.763 --> 27:59.329
of your nephew.

27:59.373 --> 28:01.549
- That's more than five times
their original offer.

28:01.592 --> 28:03.072
- I believe they
may have been swayed

28:03.116 --> 28:05.205
by the Edmund Ross affair.

28:05.248 --> 28:07.947
Very big piece of business.

28:07.990 --> 28:10.340
- They know about
your involvement?

28:10.384 --> 28:12.386
- I may have mentioned it.

28:12.429 --> 28:14.736
It all reflects well
on you, Sergeant Bell.

28:14.780 --> 28:16.738
- And there's still
the little matter of the--

28:16.782 --> 28:20.002
- The apology, indeed.

28:20.046 --> 28:21.569
Would Damon
be willing to accept

28:21.612 --> 28:22.918
the carefully-written statement

28:22.962 --> 28:24.964
that acknowledges
this never would have happened

28:25.007 --> 28:29.359
were he not a young, Black man?
- I think he might.

28:30.926 --> 28:32.449
- Ayanna?

28:32.493 --> 28:35.539
- I'm happy
if Damon and Denise are.

28:35.583 --> 28:38.151
- Then I venture
this was good news.

28:38.194 --> 28:40.719
♪

28:42.938 --> 28:44.461
- Raki.

28:44.505 --> 28:46.550
Nectar of the
Albanian gods, right?

28:48.727 --> 28:51.817
- It's lion's milk.
Makes you strong.

28:53.601 --> 28:55.472
- There a reason
why you gotta be strong?

28:59.868 --> 29:02.653
You ain't gotta
tell me nothing, man,

29:02.697 --> 29:04.177
but if you do,

29:04.220 --> 29:06.483
I just want you to know
it ain't gonna leave this bar.

29:11.488 --> 29:14.622
- Albi ordered me to do a job.
- Mm-hmm.

29:14.665 --> 29:18.408
- Said Kosta
chose me special for it.

29:18.452 --> 29:20.671
- So you gotta do it, right?
- Yeah, I gotta do it.

29:20.715 --> 29:22.412
- Yeah.

29:22.456 --> 29:24.371
- I mean, I gotta get
back in his good graces.

29:24.414 --> 29:26.242
I gotta shine
for once, you know?

29:26.286 --> 29:27.635
- Yeah.

29:27.678 --> 29:28.897
- And if he picked me,
that means he's ready

29:28.941 --> 29:30.638
to move me up
if I do a good job, right?

29:30.681 --> 29:32.335
- Yeah. So what's the problem?

29:34.207 --> 29:37.123
- It's high-risk.
- Mm-hmm.

29:37.166 --> 29:38.820
- Just not sure
I can pull it off.

29:38.864 --> 29:40.300
- No, no, no.

29:40.343 --> 29:42.128
Hey, Reg, I believe in you,
man, so whatever it is,

29:42.171 --> 29:45.653
I know you can do this.
I know it.

29:45.696 --> 29:46.872
- If I don't do it,
somebody else will.

29:46.915 --> 29:48.090
- Mm-hmm.
- Right?

29:48.134 --> 29:49.526
- Mm-hmm.

29:49.570 --> 29:52.486
- And then he'll just
keep passing me over,

29:52.529 --> 29:56.533
and I'll just stay
where I've always been.

29:56.577 --> 29:59.885
- Whatever you need,
I'm there for you.

29:59.928 --> 30:02.061
- I'm supposed to do it alone.
- So do it alone.

30:02.104 --> 30:03.149
You know,
I don't want the credit.

30:03.192 --> 30:04.933
I'm just letting you know.

30:04.977 --> 30:08.371
Whatever it is, you know,
tell me what you need.

30:10.852 --> 30:12.375
Whatever you need.

30:13.986 --> 30:15.161
- Why?

30:15.204 --> 30:17.424
[tense music]

30:17.467 --> 30:19.556
- What do you mean why?

30:19.600 --> 30:20.688
Why?

30:25.127 --> 30:27.738
What we've been through,
you and me,

30:27.782 --> 30:30.524
all the things
that you've done for me.

30:30.567 --> 30:32.308
'Cause you're my boy,
that's why.

30:32.352 --> 30:38.401
♪

30:38.445 --> 30:42.318
- All my life,
all I've ever been taught

30:42.362 --> 30:44.799
was to trust only family.

30:44.843 --> 30:46.235
- I get it, man.

30:51.719 --> 30:54.417
- It's times like these I wish
my father was still around.

30:59.074 --> 31:01.033
- You know, Reg,

31:01.076 --> 31:03.949
that Louis kid,

31:03.992 --> 31:06.038
coming around, telling me
that he's my son,

31:06.081 --> 31:08.736
and I got no fatherly feelings
towards that dude whatsoever.

31:08.779 --> 31:09.868
But you?

31:13.828 --> 31:15.308
You're my family.

31:15.351 --> 31:22.445
♪

31:23.229 --> 31:24.404
- Yeah.

31:25.796 --> 31:26.754
[grunts]

31:29.496 --> 31:31.454
- So you gonna tell me
what the job is or what?

31:38.026 --> 31:39.549
- Okay, people, let's move.

31:39.593 --> 31:42.552
This hit is going down
in real time as we speak.

31:42.596 --> 31:44.119
- Does Garcia have security?

31:44.163 --> 31:45.642
- One rent-a-cop

31:45.686 --> 31:46.948
who seems like he's watched
too many war movies.

31:46.992 --> 31:49.429
- Designated shooter
is Reggie Bogdani.

31:49.472 --> 31:50.952
- Why would Kosta give
a buffoon like Bogdani

31:50.996 --> 31:52.388
such a big job?

31:52.432 --> 31:54.390
- Stabler's theory is
that Bogdani is expendable,

31:54.434 --> 31:56.958
which means they'll
let him go down shooting.

31:57.002 --> 31:58.264
Stay sharp.

31:58.307 --> 32:01.528
[dramatic music]

32:04.444 --> 32:04.835
.

32:04.879 --> 32:07.577
[suspenseful music]

32:07.621 --> 32:14.802
♪

32:19.807 --> 32:21.374
- Garcia's at a campaign stop,

32:21.417 --> 32:23.028
and Stabler's on his way
to intercept him.

32:23.071 --> 32:25.117
- I've got a Twitter hit
on Garcia.

32:25.160 --> 32:28.337
"Just left the park
with my amazing volunteers."

32:28.381 --> 32:29.643
Tracking him.

32:29.686 --> 32:32.341
♪

32:32.385 --> 32:34.474
- Come on, Eddie.

32:34.517 --> 32:37.477
[phone ringing]

32:37.520 --> 32:39.392
Eddie, what the hell, man?

32:39.435 --> 32:40.959
If I drive around this block
one more time,

32:41.002 --> 32:42.699
I'm gonna go bananas.
- Just hang tight.

32:42.743 --> 32:44.919
I got my eyes on Garcia.

32:44.963 --> 32:46.790
- Mr. Garcia,
this is Sergeant Bell.

32:46.834 --> 32:48.096
- I'm on my way
to a book signing.

32:48.140 --> 32:49.532
Can I get back to you--

32:49.576 --> 32:51.099
- I want you to listen
to me very carefully.

32:51.143 --> 32:52.796
There's an assassin
with a screw loose

32:52.840 --> 32:55.451
that's ready to take you out
when you get to your home.

32:55.495 --> 32:58.802
A detective and an ESU team
has been dispatched to your car

32:58.846 --> 33:00.108
and to your residence.

33:00.152 --> 33:02.197
Is there anyone
at your house right now?

33:02.241 --> 33:04.286
- I told you, Sergeant,
I have my own security,

33:04.330 --> 33:05.984
and he's more than capable of--

33:06.027 --> 33:07.724
- Mr. Garcia,
please listen to me.

33:07.768 --> 33:10.031
- Terry Garcia.
- Hey, whoa.

33:10.075 --> 33:11.163
- Hey, hey!
- Take it easy.

33:11.206 --> 33:12.773
I'm a cop.
I'm a cop!

33:12.816 --> 33:14.818
Mr. Garcia,
I work for Sergeant Bell.

33:14.862 --> 33:17.299
NYPD.
Tell your man to stand down.

33:17.343 --> 33:18.561
- It's all right.

33:21.564 --> 33:22.565
I told your Sergeant--

33:22.609 --> 33:23.871
- I don't care
what you told her.

33:23.914 --> 33:25.394
There's a man from the K-O
coming to kill you

33:25.438 --> 33:27.135
because you shot
your mouth off.

33:27.179 --> 33:28.963
Is anyone
at your house right now?

33:29.007 --> 33:30.051
Wife, kids?

33:30.095 --> 33:31.270
- My kids are gone
for the weekend,

33:31.313 --> 33:34.142
and my wife is volunteering.

33:34.186 --> 33:36.101
But, actually, she might
be getting back right now--

33:36.144 --> 33:37.406
- Call her right now.
Tell her not to go home.

33:37.450 --> 33:40.801
Get in the car, please.
You too.

33:40.844 --> 33:41.802
Call her now.

33:41.845 --> 33:48.939
♪

33:51.029 --> 33:53.118
[sharp ringing]

33:53.161 --> 33:55.033
- [humming nervously]

33:55.076 --> 33:57.252
How many times can I
drive around this thing?

33:57.296 --> 33:59.385
It's like
a freaking ice cream truck.

34:01.474 --> 34:03.389
[phone ringing]

34:03.432 --> 34:06.740
All right, Reg, come on.
You got this.

34:06.783 --> 34:07.697
You got this.
[car horn blares]

34:07.741 --> 34:09.569
Hey, watch out!

34:09.612 --> 34:12.267
- Okay, Stabler's with Garcia.
- Close call.

34:12.311 --> 34:14.008
- Our man
intercepted the target.

34:14.052 --> 34:15.531
Has ESU secured the residence?

34:15.575 --> 34:18.056
- There's an accident
on the Westside Highway.

34:18.099 --> 34:19.927
SRG is sending a backup unit.

34:24.366 --> 34:26.107
- There you are.

34:26.151 --> 34:30.372
♪

34:30.416 --> 34:34.072
Yeah, yeah, let's do this.
Let's do this.

34:36.117 --> 34:37.553
[phone ringing]

34:37.597 --> 34:40.121
- Pick up the phone, Diana!
Pick up the phone!

34:40.165 --> 34:42.167
- Shoot. Hey, Reggie!

34:42.210 --> 34:45.648
- It's on, Eddie.
It's shine time now.

34:45.692 --> 34:46.823
- Reggie, listen to me,

34:46.867 --> 34:48.129
listen to me,
you're wasted, man.

34:48.173 --> 34:50.131
I got Garcia
right in front of me in a car.

34:50.175 --> 34:52.307
- Just hang tight.
Wait for my signal.

34:52.351 --> 34:55.354
- No, bro, I saw him go in now.
I'm making my move.

34:55.397 --> 34:58.792
- No, Reggie, you didn't.
Reggie, Reggie!

34:58.835 --> 35:02.752
♪

35:02.796 --> 35:03.753
[tires squeal]

35:03.797 --> 35:04.754
[car horn blares]

35:04.798 --> 35:07.757
[intense music]

35:07.801 --> 35:09.063
- Come on. Come on.

35:09.107 --> 35:10.412
Pick up, pick up, pick up.

35:10.456 --> 35:12.110
Pick up the phone.
Pick up the phone.

35:12.153 --> 35:14.547
[phone ringing]

35:16.940 --> 35:18.812
Pick up the phone.
[doorbell rings]

35:18.855 --> 35:21.423
[phone ringing]

35:25.427 --> 35:27.647
Pick up the phone.
Pick up the phone.

35:27.690 --> 35:28.735
♪

35:28.778 --> 35:32.956
[phone ringing]
[doorbell ringing]

35:33.000 --> 35:34.349
- Hi, babe.

35:34.393 --> 35:35.959
- Hey.
Where are you right now?

35:36.003 --> 35:37.309
- I just got home.

35:37.352 --> 35:39.267
Hang on, one sec.
I'm just getting a delivery.

35:39.311 --> 35:41.226
- Diana, don't open the door!

35:41.269 --> 35:43.358
- Hello?
Do I need to sign for it?

35:43.402 --> 35:45.143
[gunshot]

35:45.186 --> 35:49.712
- No, no, no!
Diana, are you okay?

35:49.756 --> 35:50.757
Diana!

35:52.889 --> 35:55.414
- [panicked breathing]
Oh.

35:55.457 --> 35:57.503
- We need to go
to my house now!

35:57.546 --> 36:04.466
♪

36:05.598 --> 36:07.948
[sirens wailing]

36:07.991 --> 36:10.211
Diana?

36:10.255 --> 36:12.082
Diana, are you okay?

36:12.126 --> 36:15.085
[solemn music]

36:15.129 --> 36:16.696
♪

36:16.739 --> 36:18.785
Diana.

36:22.223 --> 36:24.530
Come on, sweetheart.
Talk to me.

36:24.573 --> 36:31.537
♪

36:32.668 --> 36:37.456
Diana, talk to me, okay?
God, please!

36:37.499 --> 36:42.678
Please, no, God!
No, no, come on!

36:42.722 --> 36:45.551
Help! Help me!

36:45.594 --> 36:47.770
Help, help!

36:51.252 --> 36:51.600
.

36:51.644 --> 36:53.646
- Can you believe this guy?

36:53.689 --> 36:55.474
Milking the death of his wife
for a photo op?

36:55.517 --> 36:57.171
Politicians,
you know what I mean?

36:58.781 --> 37:01.915
- My nephew
really screwed this up.

37:01.958 --> 37:04.134
- I don't know about that.

37:04.178 --> 37:05.440
- What do you mean?

37:05.484 --> 37:08.487
- Well, if he did his job
and took out Garcia,

37:08.530 --> 37:10.445
it'd be over.

37:10.489 --> 37:13.535
That scum wouldn't
feel a thing.

37:13.579 --> 37:15.929
This way,
he can suffer a while,

37:15.972 --> 37:18.758
and then we send somebody
capable to finish the job.

37:18.801 --> 37:20.629
- There will be
no mistake next time

37:20.673 --> 37:23.850
because I will do it myself.

37:23.893 --> 37:27.419
- That's good.
That's what I like to hear.

37:27.462 --> 37:28.898
[suspenseful music]

37:28.942 --> 37:32.902
Meantime, Edmund Ross.

37:32.946 --> 37:35.035
- They're still holding him,
which means

37:35.078 --> 37:37.777
he must be making a deal.
You agree?

37:37.820 --> 37:40.040
- Yeah, that rich candy ass
is too soft for prison.

37:40.083 --> 37:43.739
He'll say anything
to get out of doing time.

37:43.783 --> 37:45.611
I need you
to take care of that too.

37:47.177 --> 37:49.528
Before he gets in front
of a grand jury.

37:49.571 --> 37:52.095
- Don't worry.
- Albi...

37:55.273 --> 37:56.752
No more mistakes.

37:58.580 --> 38:00.495
- You have my word, Jon.

38:00.539 --> 38:07.676
♪

38:14.596 --> 38:17.295
[reporters
questioning indistinctly]

38:30.786 --> 38:32.135
- This afternoon,

38:32.179 --> 38:37.227
my beautiful,
brilliant wife Diana

38:37.271 --> 38:38.968
volunteered
at a women's shelter

38:39.012 --> 38:42.320
as she's done twice a week
for the past five years.

38:44.800 --> 38:46.715
Two hours later,
she was murdered

38:46.759 --> 38:48.413
with a bullet
that was meant for me.

38:48.456 --> 38:52.460
I wish that bullet
had struck me instead of her

38:52.504 --> 38:54.244
with all my heart.

38:54.288 --> 38:56.769
I will not rest
until the cowards

38:56.812 --> 38:58.814
who did this
are brought to justice.

38:58.858 --> 39:01.904
[reporters
questioning indistinctly]

39:05.343 --> 39:07.257
[indistinct chatter]

39:07.301 --> 39:10.260
[dramatic music]

39:10.304 --> 39:12.393
- Hey, hit me
with one more, please.

39:15.831 --> 39:18.007
Hey. I said hit me again.

39:18.051 --> 39:19.661
- Take it easy, bro.
It's happy hour.

39:19.705 --> 39:22.142
Be happy.

39:22.185 --> 39:24.884
- You got a problem, chief?
Huh?

39:24.927 --> 39:26.755
- Yo, Reggie!

39:28.278 --> 39:30.106
- Eddie?

39:31.499 --> 39:32.848
My man.

39:34.589 --> 39:36.243
[chuckles]

39:40.726 --> 39:44.338
- Reggie Bogdani,
you're under arrest.

39:46.122 --> 39:48.473
You have the right
to remain silent.

39:48.516 --> 39:55.697
♪

40:19.286 --> 40:21.854
- I thought you were
gonna be here an hour ago.

40:21.897 --> 40:23.595
- Yeah, well, I got held up.

40:23.638 --> 40:26.424
- Is this enough lighter fluid?

40:26.467 --> 40:28.513
- Yeah, it's fine.

40:28.556 --> 40:30.732
- Well, how about you
teach me how to use it?

40:30.776 --> 40:32.691
- [chuckles]
How to use it?

40:32.734 --> 40:34.736
You put it on the coals,
you light it,

40:34.780 --> 40:36.390
you throw the burner on top.

40:36.434 --> 40:39.175
- No, you know what I mean.
Like, Eddie Ashes stuff.

40:39.219 --> 40:42.396
- Some other day.
- No, no.

40:45.007 --> 40:46.487
Not until you keep
your promise to me.

40:46.531 --> 40:49.969
- Look, Louis, not every kid
needs to grow up

40:50.012 --> 40:52.841
to be like their father.
Just take my word for it.

40:52.885 --> 40:55.757
- I don't want to be
like my father.

40:55.801 --> 40:59.021
My father
was an abusive sociopath.

41:01.110 --> 41:02.851
I want to be like you.

41:04.462 --> 41:06.072
I don't know who you are,

41:06.115 --> 41:08.378
but I know
you're not Eddie Wagner.

41:08.422 --> 41:13.209
♪

41:20.608 --> 41:23.568
[dramatic music]

41:23.611 --> 41:30.488
♪

41:50.638 --> 41:53.554
[wolf howls]
